import pandas as pd

data = {
    'Name': ['Alice', 'Bob', 'Charlie'],
    'Age': [24, 30, 22],
    'City': ['New York', 'Los Angeles', 'Chicago']
}

df = pd.DataFrame(data)

print("Full DataFrame:")
print(df)

print("\nName column:")
print(df['Name'])

print("\nFirst row of the DataFrame:")
print(df.loc[0])


OUTPUT :
Full DataFrame:
      Name  Age         City
0    Alice   24     New York
1      Bob   30  Los Angeles
2  Charlie   22      Chicago

Name column:
0      Alice
1        Bob
2    Charlie
Name: Name, dtype: object

First row of the DataFrame:
Name       Alice
Age           24
City    New York
Name: 0, dtype: object
